i dont want to hurt someone for having a different opinion
YOURE NOT STUPID for not agreeing with someone else
body:
Friendly Reminder

I feel like this one should be really obvious, but I’ve been seeing a lot of this lately, so please, don’t interact with someone’s post if it’s only to show what a lonely, pretentous, self-absorbed jack ass you are. We weren’t raised in barns and told to have zero common decency. A little goes a long way and it doesnt hurt you, when you see a post you disagree with or don’t like, to block the user or just keep scrolling. Or even private message someone if it really bothers you so much.

But reposting with snarky anti tags (or accusing someone of being a Trump supporter—I wish I was kidding but I’ve honestly seen this) or going out of your way to try and cause a fight is extremely petty and something I’m sure none of us would want for ourselves. Have an ounce of integerity. Or maybe two brain cells to rub together. Be decent.

summary: Discovering the MCU: Captain America: The Winter Soldier Welcome back to ‘Discovering the MCU’! Previous posts: Phase 1, Iron...
caption:
Discovering the MCU: Captain America: The Winter Soldier

Welcome back to ‘Discovering the MCU’! Previous posts: Phase 1, Iron Man 3, Thor: The Dark World

Note: This review contains spoilers for ‘Captain America: The Winter Soldier’.

I really enjoyed ‘Winter Soldier’. It contains everything I could really ask for; plot twists, character development, a decent villain(s), and some pretty great action.

The action scenes are pretty awesome in this film. The stuff that both Cap and Natasha get to do are fucking badass, and the choreography is great. Instead of slowly building up to a massive final battle, the action starts from the very beginning, and never slows down much.

I liked that we see some character development, especially with Black Widow. I really enjoyed her role in this movie and the progression of the friendship between her and Steve.

The story is good, and the plot is nice and twisty, even if most of the twists were not entirely unpredictable (I knew Fury couldn’t be dead!) The whole movie is thoroughly exciting. I liked it.😄
